@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Home Page";
}

<div class="jumbotron">
    <h1>Campaigns RPG toolkit</h1>
    <p class="lead">Quickly handle the complexities of managing your campaign's characters</p>
</div>

<div class="row">
    <div class="col-sm-4 col-md-4">
        <div class="thumbnail">
            <div class="caption">
                <h3>An excuse to use new technologies</h3>
                <p>This is really just a testbed for some ASP.Net, Web API, MVC, SignalR and Angular.js experimentation.</p>
                <p>You can browse the source code on the <a href="https://github.com/seshbot/campaigns">GitHub repository</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-4 col-md-4">
        <div class="thumbnail">
            <div class="caption">
                <h3>Create a Gaming Session</h3>
                <p>The @Html.ActionLink("Sessions", "Index", "Sessions") area allows you to create a page for a group of people to write messages and roll dice (no login required.)</p>
                <p><a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Sessions")" class="btn btn-default" role="button">Browse Sessions</a> <a href="@Url.Action("Create", "Sessions")" class="btn btn-primary" role="button">Create a Session</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-sm-4 col-md-4">
        <div class="thumbnail">
            <div class="caption">
                <h3>Create Character Sheets</h3>
                <p>Still a work in progress, this area will allow the creation of character sheets using various rulesets (e.g., D&amp;D 5E) and level them up over time.</p>
                <p>This area will also allow for inventory management and tracking the effects of spells and items on your characters statistics.</p>
                <p><a href="@Url.Action("Index", "CharacterSheets")" class="btn btn-default" role="button">Browse Characters</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>